xchanging imagined futures. Shifting the emphasis from adoption's outcome to its conditions of possibility, this insightful ethnography places the practice of domestic adoption within a temporal, economic, and affective framework in order to interrogate the social inequality and power dynamics that render adoption-and the families it produces-possible.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aInterracial adoptionzUnited Statesy21st century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  a21st century.  aadoption agency.  aadoption process.  aamerica.  aanticipation.  aclass.  adomestic adoption.  aexpectant mothers.  afamily.  aideologies.  ainstitutional structures.  aintimate speculation.  ainvestment.  amediating relationships.  aobservation.  apower dynamics.  aprofessionals.  aprospective adopters.  arace.  asocial inequality.  asocial workers.  atransracial adoption.  aunited states.  awho can have a future.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCA Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065207908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066763940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520971240zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520971240423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520971240.jpg  a978-3-11-061013